    <title>Vetoed Draft Resolutions in the United Nations Security Council 1946-2012</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;This paper records draft resolutions vetoed in the Security Council between 1946 and 2012. It is preceded by a short account of the way the veto has been used by the Council’s five Permanent Members: China, France, Russia (the Soviet Union until 1991), the United Kingdom and the United States.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
